{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2006 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record=8-5 |ConfRecord=3-5 |HeadCoach=[[Steve Spurrier]] |DefCoach=[[Tyrone Nix]] |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) |Champion=Liberty Bowl Champions |BowlTourney=[[2006 Liberty Bowl|Liberty Bowl]] vs. [[2006 Houston Cougars football team|Houston]] |BowlTourneyResult=W 44-36 }} {{2006 SEC football standings}} The '''2006 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[Southeastern Conference]] during the [[college football]] [[2006 NCAA Division I FBS football season|season of 2006-2007]]. The Gamecocks were led by [[Steve Spurrier]] in his second season as USC head coach and played their home games in [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]].
==Schedule== The October 28 game against Tennessee played host to ESPN's [[College Gameday]], the third year in a row that South Carolina had hosted the program.
